		<profileDesc>
			<abstract><p>A Gǝʿǝz French Amharic dictionary  dictionary (only letters ሀ to ረ) compiled in
        Ethiopia by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9683Urbino">Father Giusto da Urbino (Jacopo Curtopassi)</persName>
      in <date>1850-1855</date>. According to the author, the rest of the dictionary was lost when he was arrested in 1855
       (<bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/JNSCTGWZ"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Wion2013Hatata1"/><title level="a">L’histoire d’un vrai faux traité philosophique (Ḥatatā Zar’a Yā‘eqob et Ḥatatā Walda Ḥeywat). Épisode 1 : Le temps de la découverte. De l’entrée en collection à l’édition scientifique (1852-1904)</title><title level="j">Afriques [online]</title><author><forename>Anaïs</forename><surname>Wion</surname></author><date>2013</date><biblScope unit="page">1-64</biblScope><note type="url">http://journals.openedition.org/afriques/1063</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Wion2013Hatata1</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Wion2013Hatata1</note><citedRange unit="number">29</citedRange></bibl>).</p></abstract>

